**Description**
 Are you an innovative creator with a passion for shaping unforgettable digital experiences? We are seeking for an Experienced Designer for the fashion industry.




 Work tasks




 We are seeking for an Experienced Designer who will elevate the design craft to consistently and effectively work across of the customer journey. As an Experience Designer you are responsible for i.e. following:




* Designing for all end-users on all digital and omni-experience touchpoints;
* Responsible for communicating customer and user needs in product context;
* Conducting initial customer research and mapping customer journeys;
* Defining future visions based on customer insights, business goals & KPIs plus technical possibilities;
* Setting user experience metrics together with the product team;
* Ensuring that design follows applicable design libraries and is connected to the Fabric Design System;
* Defining intuitive flows, delivering clear wireframes, interaction design and low and high-fidelity prototypes;
* Facilitating design sprints and workshops;
* Overall advocating Customer-centered design solutions.


**Qualifications**
* Ability to simplify complexity and facilitate collaborative workshops (e.g., Design Sprints) with stakeholders;
* Ability to utilize data for decision-making and collaborate with analytics and A/B testers;
* Ability in translating qualitative and quantitative customer data into actionable insights;
* Lean UX Methods – from idea to code as fast as possible;
* Applying user-centered design principles, problem-solving, design thinking, and design strategy:
* Iteratively testing solutions with customer to improve designs;
* Agile customer insights;
* Proficiency in tools like Figma, Miro, and User Zoom for user testing.
* Conducting trend analysis, benchmarking, and competitive analysis to inform design decisions;
* Possessing knowledge of the retail industry, customer journey, and customer lifetime value.


 Terms




 You will be employed by Q working on an assignment at a customer in Stockholm. We are going throgh applications continously and are presenting candidates, we are thefore looking forward to recieve your application as soon as possibile.




 Q har kollektivavtal och är medlem i branschorganisationen Almega samt i Svenskt Näringsliv. Företaget erbjuder interims- och rekryteringslösningar inom branscherna IT, teknik, administration, ekonomi, industri samt lager/logistik med personallösningar inom olika befattningsnivåer.




